# CLAUDE.local.md

> **Builder-mode context.** Loaded into Claude Code sessions on **your machine only** (gitignored). Anyone who clones this repo without running `./bootstrap.sh` will not see this content. That isolation is intentional: builders see the playbook and architecture history; subagents at runtime do not.
>
> If you didn't intend to be in builder mode (e.g. you're a teammate who just wants to run an agent), delete this file or rename it.

## Method

The team's agent-building method lives in the playbook below. Read it first; the rules in `CLAUDE.md` and this file *extend* it with project-specific conventions, never duplicate it.

@docs/playbook/PLAYBOOK.md

## Builder Invariants

- **The LikeC4 model is structural canon — auto-imported every session.** Do not autonomously edit it as part of a bug fix. If a fix requires a model change, stop and ask the operator.

> *Add project-specific builder invariants here. Things like: which tests are mandatory before committing, which files require ADRs to change, which CLIs must stay backward-compatible.*

## Architecture (LikeC4)

The structural model is auto-loaded into every builder session via the `@imports` below. This is authoritative for components, boundaries, and ownership. Run `npx likec4 validate` after editing any `.c4` file and before committing.

